               Documentation for "schemes" script v0.0.1
                     Marc Feeley (August 7, 2009)

Download from: http://www.iro.umontreal.ca/~feeley/schemes-v0_0_1.tgz

The "schemes" shell script automates the installation of a wide
variety of implementations of the Scheme programming language on Unix
compatible platforms, which is particularly useful to test the
portability of Scheme programs and to evaluate Scheme systems.  The
script automatically downloads from the system's web page the latest
version of the system to be installed, compiles it and installs it
locally (in the sys subdirectory of this directory).  The script can
also be used to detect which Scheme systems are currently installed.

Version 0.0.1 of the "schemes" script supports 14 Scheme systems:

  Bigloo
  Chicken
  Gambit
  Gauche
  Kawa
  Larceny
  MIT Scheme
  MzScheme
  Scheme48
  SCM
  Scsh
  SISC
  Stalin
  STklos

There is partial support for the following Scheme systems:

  Chez Scheme
  Guile
  Ikarus
  Petite Chez Scheme
  RScheme
  Ypsilon

If you are interested in having support for these or other unsupported
Scheme systems, or you want to contribute an improvement, please
modify the script accordingly and send your modifications to
feeley@iro.umontreal.ca for inclusion in future versions of the
script.

Here is a sample use of the script.

% ./schemes --query
Searching for the Scheme systems accessible in the current PATH:
  Bigloo 3.1b            -> /usr/local/bin/bigloo
  Chicken 3.4.0          -> /usr/local/bin/csi
  Chicken compiler 3.4.0 -> /usr/local/bin/csc
  Gambit 4.5.1           -> /usr/bin/gsi
  Gambit compiler 4.5.1  -> /usr/bin/gsc
  MIT Scheme 7.7.90.+    -> /usr/local/bin/mit-scheme
  Scheme48 1.8           -> /usr/local/bin/scheme48
% ./schemes --supported
 bigloo chicken gambit gauche kawa larceny mit mzscheme scheme48 scm scsh sisc stalin stklos
% ./schemes --install --supported

*** Installing: bigloo chicken gambit gauche kawa larceny mit mzscheme scheme48 scm scsh sisc stalin stklos

************************************************************** bigloo
*** Downloading bigloo from http://www-sop.inria.fr/mimosa/fp/Bigloo/
*** Dowloaded files:
total 25520
-rw-r--r--  1 feeley  feeley  13062630 Aug  7 10:44 bigloo3.2b-2.tar.gz
*** Installing bigloo

... lots of stuff removed

